<li id="cite_note-29"><b><a href="#cite_ref-29" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web" id="CITEREFClinton.2C_Bill">Clinton, Bill. <a href="http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-srv/politics/special/states/docs/sou94.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-srv/politics/special/states/docs/sou94.htm" rel="nofollow">"1994 State Of The Union Address"</a><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-srv/politics/special/states/docs/sou94.htm" class="external free" title="http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-srv/politics/special/states/docs/sou94.htm" rel="nofollow">http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-srv/politics/special/states/docs/sou94.htm</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2006-01-22</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=1994+State+Of+The+Union+Address&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.aulast=Clinton%2C+Bill&amp;rft.au=Clinton%2C+Bill&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Fwp-srv%2Fpolitics%2Fspecial%2Fstates%2Fdocs%2Fsou94.htm&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Democratic_peace_theory"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-30"><b><a href="#cite_ref-30" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web"><a href="http://www.whitehouse.gov/news/releases/2004/11/20041112-5.html" class="external text" title="http://www.whitehouse.gov/news/releases/2004/11/20041112-5.html" rel="nofollow">"President and Prime Minister Blair Discussed Iraq, Middle East"</a><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.whitehouse.gov/news/releases/2004/11/20041112-5.html" class="external free" title="http://www.whitehouse.gov/news/releases/2004/11/20041112-5.html" rel="nofollow">http://www.whitehouse.gov/news/releases/2004/11/20041112-5.html</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on October 3 2005</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=President+and+Prime+Minister+Blair+Discussed+Iraq%2C+Middle+East&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.whitehouse.gov%2Fnews%2Freleases%2F2004%2F11%2F20041112-5.html&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Democratic_peace_theory"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-31"><b><a href="#cite_ref-31" title="">^</a></b> "History has taught us democracies don't war. Democracies -- you don't run for office in a democracy and say, please vote for me, I promise you war. (Laughter.) You run for office in democracies, and say, vote for me, I'll represent your interests; vote for me, I'll help your young girls go to school, or the health care you get improved." <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web"><a href="http://www.whitehouse.gov/news/releases/2006/03/20060301-3.html" class="external text" title="http://www.whitehouse.gov/news/releases/2006/03/20060301-3.html" rel="nofollow">"President Thanks U.S. and Coalition Troops in Afghanistan"</a><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.whitehouse.gov/news/releases/2006/03/20060301-3.html" class="external free" title="http://www.whitehouse.gov/news/releases/2006/03/20060301-3.html" rel="nofollow">http://www.whitehouse.gov/news/releases/2006/03/20060301-3.html</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on December 26 2008</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=President+Thanks+U.S.+and+Coalition+Troops+in+Afghanistan&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.whitehouse.gov%2Fnews%2Freleases%2F2006%2F03%2F20060301-3.html&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Democratic_peace_theory"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-32"><b><a href="#cite_ref-32" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web"><a href="http://www.fas.org/asmp/resources/govern/109th/S516is.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.fas.org/asmp/resources/govern/109th/S516is.htm" rel="nofollow">"109th Congress, 1st Session, S. 516"</a><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.fas.org/asmp/resources/govern/109th/S516is.htm" class="external free" title="http://www.fas.org/asmp/resources/govern/109th/S516is.htm" rel="nofollow">http://www.fas.org/asmp/resources/govern/109th/S516is.htm</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on August 19 2006</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=109th+Congress%2C+1st+Session%2C+S.+516&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.fas.org%2Fasmp%2Fresources%2Fgovern%2F109th%2FS516is.htm&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Democratic_peace_theory"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-33"><b><a href="#cite_ref-33" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web"><a href="http://ec.europa.eu/comm/external_relations/news/patten/speech_99_193.htm" class="external text" title="http://ec.europa.eu/comm/external_relations/news/patten/speech_99_193.htm" rel="nofollow">"Human Rights Discussion Forum; Speech by The Rt Hon Chris Patten, CH. Plenary Session Brussels - Charlemagne building - 30 November 1999 - SPEECH/99/193"</a><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://ec.europa.eu/comm/external_relations/news/patten/speech_99_193.htm" class="external free" title="http://ec.europa.eu/comm/external_relations/news/patten/speech_99_193.htm" rel="nofollow">http://ec.europa.eu/comm/external_relations/news/patten/speech_99_193.htm</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on August 19 2006</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Human+Rights+Discussion+Forum%3B+Speech+by+The+Rt+Hon+Chris+Patten%2C+CH.+Plenary+Session+Brussels+-+Charlemagne+building+-+30+November+1999+-+SPEECH%2F99%2F193&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fec.europa.eu%2Fcomm%2Fexternal_relations%2Fnews%2Fpatten%2Fspeech_99_193.htm&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Democratic_peace_theory"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-34"><b><a href="#cite_ref-34" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web"><a href="http://ec.europa.eu/comm/external_relations/us/intro/peace.htm" class="external text" title="http://ec.europa.eu/comm/external_relations/us/intro/peace.htm" rel="nofollow">"A Secure Europe in a Better World: European Security Strategy. Brussels, 12 December 2003"</a><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://ec.europa.eu/comm/external_relations/us/intro/peace.htm" class="external free" title="http://ec.europa.eu/comm/external_relations/us/intro/peace.htm" rel="nofollow">http://ec.europa.eu/comm/external_relations/us/intro/peace.htm</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on August 19 2006</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=A+Secure+Europe+in+a+Better+World%3A+European+Security+Strategy.+Brussels%2C+12+December+2003&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fec.europa.eu%2Fcomm%2Fexternal_relations%2Fus%2Fintro%2Fpeace.htm&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Democratic_peace_theory"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-35"><b><a href="#cite_ref-35" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://www.thedailyshow.com/video/index.jhtml?videoId=185185&amp;title=Tony-Blair-Pt.-1" class="external text" title="http://www.thedailyshow.com/video/index.jhtml?videoId=185185&amp;title=Tony-Blair-Pt.-1" rel="nofollow">Interview</a> in <i><a href="/wiki/The_Daily_Show_with_Jon_Stewart" title="The Daily Show with Jon Stewart" class="mw-redirect">The Daily Show with Jon Stewart</a></i> 18 September 2008</li>
<li id="cite_note-36"><b><a href="#cite_ref-36" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://historymatters.gmu.edu/d/4943/" class="external text" title="http://historymatters.gmu.edu/d/4943/" rel="nofollow">Wilson, T. Woodrow: <i>Message to Congress</i> April 2, 1917</a> According to <a href="/wiki/Richard_Nixon" title="Richard Nixon">Richard Nixon</a>, Wilson also stated "a war to end war"<a href="http://www.presidency.ucsb.edu/ws/index.php?pid=2303}" class="external text" title="http://www.presidency.ucsb.edu/ws/index.php?pid=2303}" rel="nofollow">Nixon, Richard M.: Televised speech, November 3, 1969</a> Wilson's vision for the world after <a href="/wiki/World_War_I" title="World War I">World War I</a>, his <a href="/wiki/Fourteen_Points" title="Fourteen Points">Fourteen Points</a>(1918), did not mention democracy, but in other aspects "sound almost as though Kant were guiding Wilson's writing hand." They included both Kant’s <a href="/wiki/Cosmopolitanism" title="Cosmopolitanism">cosmopolitan</a> law and pacific union. The third of the <a href="/wiki/Fourteen_Points" title="Fourteen Points">Fourteen Points</a> specified the removal of economic barriers between peaceful nations; the fourteenth provided for the <a href="/wiki/League_of_Nations" title="League of Nations">League of Nations</a> (Russett 1993).</li>
<li id="cite_note-37"><b><a href="#cite_ref-37" title="">^</a></b> It is probably fair to say that a majority of authors agree that economic wealth is an important prerequisite for full democratization, while a significant minority does not.</li>
</ol>
</div>
